Write a Java program to find and print all the leader elements in an integer array.
       A leader element is defined as an element that is greater than all the elements to its right in the array.
       For example, if the input array is {1, 2, 3, 23, 6, 15, 14, 19}.
       the output should be 23, 15, 19 as these elements are greater than all the elements to their right.


