Write a Java program to remove duplicate elements from an array and return a new array containing only the unique elements using a method. 

    Assume that the original array contains integers. For example, if the input array is {1, 2, 3, 1, 2, 1, 4}, the program should return a new array {1, 2, 3, 4}.



    Your task is to implement the method removeDuplicates(int[] arr) that takes an array of integers arr as input and returns a new array with duplicate elements removed.

    Make sure to provide the complete Java program with the method implementation.
