 Write a Java program that finds and prints all groups of four elements in an integer array whose sum equals a given target number. 
       Given an array of integers and a target sum, the program should identify and output all combinations of four elements from the array whose sum is equal to the given target.
       For example, if the input array is {10, 20, 30, 40, 1, 2} and the target sum is 53.
       the output should be:
       Groups of four elements whose sum is 53:
       [10, 40, 1, 2]
       [20, 30, 1, 2]

